ope Cruz and Alfredo Landa, to Pedro Almodóvar, Carlos Saura and Alejandro Amenábar. The fine-grained study of acting in each chapter also provides a means of exploring broader questions surrounding Spanish film practices, culture and society.Performance and Spanish film will be essential reading for both students and scholars of Spanish film alike, as well as to those more broadly interested in the history of screen acting.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture acting. 0aMotion pictures, SpanishxHistory. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aActors.  aPerformance techniques.  aPerformance.  aScreen acting.  aSpanish film.1 aAllbritton, Dean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllbritton, Dean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCiller, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelgado, Maria M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEpps, Brad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaulkner, Sally, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFouz-Hernández, Santiago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Stuart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelero, Alejandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelero, Alejandro, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMira, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStone, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVernon, Kathleen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheeler, Duncan, econtributor.